FT  08 SEP 94 / International Company News: Air Canada 'to double income'
Air Canada will double operating income to between CDollars 140m (USDollars
102m) and CDollars 150m this year and report a small final net profit, said
Mr Hollis Harris, chairman, writes Robert Gibbens in Montreal.
Continental Airlines of the US, which is 20 per cent-owned by Air Canada,
will lose about USDollars 100m but return to profitability in 1995, he said.
